<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zimbabwe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mugabe: Opposition Manipulated by Whites </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mugabe: Opposition Manipulated by Whites </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2805124594 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1030 GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2805124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe has said his 
political opponents are being manipulated by whites in the 
country, who are once more resorting to racial arguments on the 
eve of elections in Zimbabwe. Speaking before Zimbabwe African 
National Union members, Mugabe said one of the examples of these 
politicians is Enoch Dumbutshena, the leader of Zimbabwe 
Movement of Unity and former chairman of the Supreme Court. 
Mugabe has been accusing the country's whites of racism for 
resisting the government's plans of acquiring agricultural land 
and distributing them to black farmers. Whites say the 
government is using the agricultural issue to restore its 
popularity before the elections. 

</TEXT>

