  [Text] In Cape Town today, Angola and South Africa signed 
an agreement establishing formal diplomatic relations between 
the two countries at ambassadorial level. The agreement was 
signed by the two countries' foreign ministers, Alfred Nzo and 
Venancio de Moura. The Angolan delegation was also greeted today 
