BFN 

  [Text] The European Union [EU] has lifted all remaining 
economic restrictions on South Africa. In a statement released 
in Johannesburg, the EU followed the decision by the UN Security 
Council to lift its own sanctions earlier this month. It was 
also motivated by the desire to assist the new South African 
Government. 

