  [Text] The IFP's [Inkatha Freedom Party] Youth Brigade says 
sit-in strikes and demonstrations will take place in 
KwaZulu/Natal unless the state of emergency is lifted. The 
brigade has called on all peace-loving South Africans to 
persuade the government to lift the state of emergency which was 
imposed two months ago. 

