<H3> <TI>   Pik Botha Elected in PWV </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pik Botha Elected in PWV </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2905071794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0600 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2905071794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mineral and Energy Affairs minister Pik Botha has 
been elected NP [National Party] leader in the PWV [Pretoria, 
Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] region. He defeated Constitutional 
Development and Provincial Affairs Minister Roelf Meyer in an 
election at the last Transvaal NP congress under the old 
dispensation. Mr. Meyer obtained fewer than 10 percent of the 
votes. 

</TEXT>

