<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] South Africa has been admitted to the Nonaligned 
Movement. The announcement was made in Cairo by Egyptian 
Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa at the opening session of a meeting 
of Nonaligned foreign ministers. After the announcement South 
African Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo was led to a seat in the 
conference hall to applause from delegates. South Africa is to 
be readmitted as a full member of the Commonwealth tomorrow. 

