<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electoral Registration To Begin; Renamo Said Resisting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electoral Registration To Begin; Renamo Said Resisting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0106100994 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0700 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0106100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Joaquim Chissano will be the first citizen 
to be registered in the Mozambican capital to vote in the 
forthcoming October elections. The president of the Republic 
will be registered in the Josina Machel School in Maputo. About 
85 percent of electoral registration posts in Maputo will begin 
operating today. The process is also scheduled to begin today in 
all provinces, although in some areas it will be delayed due to 
logistical problems. In some provinces, the Mozambique National 
Resistance has not permitted the beginning of electoral 
registration in areas under its control. 

</TEXT>

