<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Ibrahim Boubacar Keita has returned 
home from Gabon, where he has just completed a five-day working 
visit. This was the first visit abroad by the head of the 
government who, in addition to discussions with the Gabonese 
authorities, met with the Malian community there. Mr. Keita, 
who returned home yesterday afternoon, stated, while taking 
stock of his visit, that the behavior of the Malian community in 
Gabon honors us. However, he added, the emigration of Malians 
to that country poses a number of problems; there is a need to 
reconsider our emigration policy. 

</TEXT>

