<F P=101> Cote d'Ivoire </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Outlines Plan for New CFA Currency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Outlines Plan for New CFA Currency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2903181894 Paris JEUNE AFRIQUE in French 24-30 Mar 94 
P4--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AB2903181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris JEUNE AFRIQUE </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ivorian President Henri Konan Bedie is planning to 
create a new CFA franc like de Gaulle did in 1959 when he 
created the new French franc. The new CFA franc will equal 100 
current CFA francs and, since it will have the same value as the 
French franc, a single currency will circulate within the franc 
zone. It will be a simple solution. The move will clearly show 
that the CFA franc, even if devalued, remains resolutely 
attached to the French franc. Also it will show that the January 
devaluation is definitely the last one. 
  The objective is to prevent any further devaluation of the 
CFA down the line and give additional support to the operation 
launched at the beginning of the year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

