<H3> <TI>   Aozou Strip Upgraded To Subprefecture Status </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aozou Strip Upgraded To Subprefecture Status </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0206102394 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 1215 GMT 1 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0206102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville Africa No. 1 </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Idriss Deby yesterday visited Aozou in 
the far north of Chad following the official restoration of the 
Aozou Strip by Libya to Chad. On that occasion, the Chadian 
head of state decided to upgrade the Aozou administrative post, 
the only locality in that 114,000-square-km desert area to 
subprefecture status. The Aozou Strip was handed over to the 
Chadian authorities yesterday after more than 20 years of Libyan 
occupation. For many people, Libya is trying, by that gesture, 
to gain increased African support in its efforts to get the 
United Nations to lift sanctions against it. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

