<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guidelines for a new training strategy for South 
Africa have been published by the Department of Manpower. 
Earlier, a task group comprising representatives of the 
National Training Board, employers, employee organizations, 
education and training institutions, and the state was appointed 
by the Minister of Manpower to investigate the issue. The 
questions investigated includes the training of educators, basic 
adult education, and legislation. The report is available from 
the state printer and reaction to it must be submitted to the 
secretary of the National Training Board at Private Bag X117, 
Pretoria, before the 20th of this month. 

