  [Text] Durban June 2 SAPA -- The KwaZulu/Natal cabinet 
decided on Thursday [2 June] afternoon not to disclose the 
subject of its talks in Pietermaritzburg during the day, a 
statement from the provincial executive said. The cabinet 
issued a statement before concluding more than four hours of 
talks. 
  Earlier, the executive met to swear in three African 
National 
