<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mandela Rules Out Sending Troops to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mandela Rules Out Sending Troops to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0306101794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0306101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Nelson Mandela has decided against sending 
South African troops to Rwanda to join a United Nations 
peacekeeping force in that country. However, speaking in an 
interview with REUTER news agency, President Mandela said South 
Africa was very interested in providing humanitarian aid. He 
said South Africa had decided to send a field hospital to help 
treat Rwandan refugees and was considering other assistance. 
South Africa would also consult the UN on what role South 
Africa could play to help end the conflict in that country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

