<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zaire </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Organizes Rally, Criticizes France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Organizes Rally, Criticizes France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0506170494 Paris AFP in French 1547 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0506170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kinshasa, 5 Jun (AFP) -- Kibassa Maliba, president 
of the Zairian Sacred Union of the Radical Opposition, USOR, 
today severely criticized France's position in Zaire. He 
accused France of "supporting the dictatorship" of President 
Mobutu. Mr. Maliba, accompanied by Etienne Tshisekedi, the main 
Zairian opposition leader, was taking part in a mammoth rally 
organized by the Union for Democracy and Social Progress, UDPS, 
the first radical opposition party, to which both belong. 
  Mr. Tshisekedi "warned" Marshal Mobutu to sign the decree 
appointing him the new prime minister of Zaire, otherwise 
threatening to call on diamond producers to embark on an 
indefinite strike. 
  Mr. Tshisekedi is a native of the Kasai-oriental region (in 
central Zaire), the main diamond producing region of the 
country, whose production currently represents the main source 
of revenue for the country. 

</TEXT>

