<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Kenya </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Moi Postpones Regional Summit on Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Moi Postpones Regional Summit on Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0306192394 Nairobi Kenya Broadcasting Corporation Network 
in English 1300 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0306192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi Kenya Broadcasting Corporation Network 
in English 1300 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Excellency President Daniel arap Moi has 
postponed the meeting originally scheduled for 6th of this month 
to deliberate on possible ways of restoring lasting peace in 
Rwanda. In a statement issued from State House, Nakuru, 
President Moi said the postponement became necessary as 
confirmation of attendance had not been received by today from 
some invited heads of state. Those invited are President Yoweri 
Museveni of Uganda, Ali Hassan Mwinyi of Tanzania, Mobutu Sese 
Seko of Zaire and acting President Sylvestre Ntibantunganya of 
Burundi. 
  He said the postponement would enable him and his colleagues 
to consult a little more to ensure that all of them attend any 
such meeting. The head of state reiterated that the problem of 
Rwanda was complicated and therefore required concerted efforts 
of all the neighboring of heads of state so that decisions 
reached might stand a better chance of success. 
  At the same time President Moi appealed to all the 
combatants 
in Rwanda to start and observe a cease-fire to avoid any more 
loss of life. He also observed that failure to take this course 
of action would mean that the leaders have no value for the 
lives of their people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

