<F P=102>   EA0306165194 Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic in 
Somali 1100 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0306165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic </F>
<F P=105>  Somali </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the 12 organizations, the Somali 
Salvation Alliance, today warmly welcomed the UN Security 
Council's resolution extending UN Operation in Somalia [UNOSOM] 
operations in Somalia, from 1 June. The spokesman said the 
resolution would greatly help the efforts being made to bring 
the Somali people together, for the reconstruction of the 
country, reconciliation and national unity. Resolution 923 
stipulates that UNOSOM would cease its operations in Somalia in 
March 1995 [as heard]. The spokesman called on all members of 
Somali society to support UNOSOM operations in the country and 
participate in the implementation of the UN Security Council 
resolution, and the peace declarations reached by leaders of 
Somali organizations regarding a lasting peace and national 
reconciliation. 

