<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Accra, June 3 (AFP) -- Ghana Friday [3 June] called 
on the international community to help end the "carnage" in 
Rwanda by putting pressure on the warring factions there, a 
Foreign Ministry communique said here. 
  Deputy Foreign Minister Mohamed Ibn Chambas told parliament 
that the belligerents must accept "the full implementation of UN 
resolutions" calling for a ceasefire in the two-month civil war. 
