<H3> <TI>   House of Representatives Asks Abacha To Leave </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House of Representatives Asks Abacha To Leave </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0306183094 Paris AFP in French 1725 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0306183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lagos, 3 Jun (AFP) -- Members of the House of 
Representatives, dissolved by the military authorities, today 
called on General Sani Abacha to relinquish power "by 11 June." 
The call was made in a communique issued at the end of a 
meeting attended by 348 members. 
  The 11 June deadline was chosen because it is the eve of the 
first anniversary of the 12 June 1993 presidential elections 
annulled by the military. 
  The results of these elections are expected to be announced 
and the winner sworn into office to form a broad-based national 
government, the communique stated. It also indicated that the 
number of delegates at the meeting was sufficient for the 
necessary quorum to be attained. 
  "The meeting came to the irrevocable conclusion that the 
current military junta lacks the necessary spirit or wisdom to 
move the country forward," the communique added. 

</TEXT>

