<F P=104>  Kaduna Radio Nigeria </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Government has declared illegal the 
proposed national industrial action planned for Thursday [9 
June] by some categories of employees of NEPA [National Electric 
Power Authority]. The minister of state for power and steel, 
Elder Wole Oyelese, told a Radio Nigeria Correspondent in Lagos 
that the proposed action was uncalled for. He explained that 
the employees were only out to create unnecessary problems for 
government. He reminded them that government will not hesitate 
to take drastic action against anyone who attempts to frustrate 
efforts aimed at installing peace and harmony in the country. 
The minister stated that everything has been done to forestall 
any disruption of electricity supply by unscrupulous elements. 

