<H3> <TI>   UNITA Attack on Cuito Repulsed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNITA Attack on Cuito Repulsed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0406124294 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1200 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0406124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Abel Abraao in Cuito] </F>
  [Text] Jonas Savimbi's men have bit the red dust of this 
bloody land as they tried to take the martyred city of Cuito by 
storm at dawn today. Those who sow the wind, reap the 
whirlwind. UNITA today got what it deserved. UNITA left 
several dead bodies behind as others fled in disarray. Today's 
clashes were the fiercest since the start of the hostilities on 
26 May. 
  Military sources with the Angolan Armed Forces Operational 
Command in Bie Province said this morning that UNITA rebels, who 
are still in the outlaying areas of the city, continue to 
receive reinforcements for yet another attack on Cuito. As we 
file this report, clashes are still in progress and UNITA 
continues to shell the city. One cannot yet take stock of the 
human and material losses of the past 24 hours. 
  In view of the unstable military situation, Belgium's 
Doctors 
Without Borders and Mr. (Hans Peter), a World Food Program 
official, left the city of Cuito for Luanda this morning. Mr. 
(Dominic Henry), delegate of the International Committee of the 
Red Cross for Bie Province, refused to leave the city. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

