<H3> <TI>   Foreign Aid Workers Evacuated From Cuito </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Aid Workers Evacuated From Cuito </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0406160794 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
1200 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0406160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A communique from the World Food Program [WFP] 
received at our news desk today reveals that eight WFP workers 
were evacuated from Cuito this morning because of intense 
clashes there. Also evacuated from Cuito were workers from the 
Doctors Without Borders organization of Belgium and Oxfam 
humanitarian organization. The communique also says that the 
United Nations continues to negotiate with the government and 
the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola with a 
view to resuming humanitarian flights soon to Huambo, Cuito, 
Malanje, and Uige. 

</TEXT>

