<H3> <TI>   `Unresolved Problems' To Delay Local Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Unresolved Problems' To Delay Local Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0306202894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0306202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A member of the Provincial Electoral Commission in 
the PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, Vereeniging], Mr. Thozamile 
Botha, says unresolved problems may prevent the holding of local 
government elections in the country, even by May next year. 
Speaking in Pretoria at a Department of Constitutional 
Development and Provincial Affairs briefing, Mr. Botha said the 
elections would definitely not take place in October and that 
even the later date was questionable. He said voter 
registration and ward delimitation were among the tasks that 
have still to be completed before local elections could take 
place. The negotiating council had earlier proposed that the 
elections be held in October. 

</TEXT>

