<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Object to SANDF Deployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Object to SANDF Deployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0406130794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 4 June 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0406130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The police in the Western Cape have objected to an 
undertaking by the ANC's regional police spokesman, Mr. Vincent 
Diba, that the National Defense Force will be deployed in the 
gang-riddled Manenberg area of the Cape Flats next week. 
  A police spokesman, Colonel Raymond (Dawoud), said 
gang-related crime was a police responsibility and not that of 
the National Defense Force, which was not trained to handle the 
situation. Speaking on behalf of the Western Cape MEC [Members 
of Executive Committee] for police, Mr. Patrick Mckenzie, Col. 
(Dawoud) appealed to people not to allow the issue to develop 
political overtones. He added that crime in the area had 
decreased significantly since the start of Operation Gang-Bust 
last week. 

</TEXT>

