<H3> <TI>   Police Find No Evidence of Plot </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Find No Evidence of Plot </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0606070494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0606070494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The police say a thorough investigation has produced 
no evidence of an alleged plot between German neo-Nazis and 
South Africa ultra right-wingers to assassinate President Nelson 
Mandela during his inauguration in Pretoria last month. 
According to a newspaper report the extremists had planned a 
mortar attack on the Union Buildings from a nearby hill. The 
police said they had followed all leads, including German 
neo-Nazi activity in South Africa. German right-wingers have 
been arrested after a gun battle with police near Pretoria, but 
there has been no evidence of assassination plans. 

</TEXT>

