<F P=104>  Addis Ababa Voice of Ethiopia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Amharic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Millions of Ethiopian voters are currently 
casting their votes throughout the country, with the exception 
of the Somali region and Dire Dawa, to elect members to the 
Constituent Assembly. Although there are 22.8 million eligible 
voters in the country, only about 15,021,581 have registered to 
vote. [passage omitted] 
  According to reports received from ETHIOPIAN NEWS AGENCY 
correspondents, people began voting even before going to church. 
No significant problems have been observed during the voting 
process; it is going smoothly and successfully. In some polling 
stations there have been problems because of a lack of stewards. 
[passage omitted] 

