<H3> <TI>   Abiola Appeals For Restraint From Supporters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abiola Appeals For Restraint From Supporters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0606183194 Kaduna Radio Nigeria in English 1700 GMT 6 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0606183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kaduna Radio Nigeria </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A former presidential candidate, Chief Moshood 
Abiola, has appealed to his supporters to refrain from media 
attacks on the Hausa-Fulanis for his failure to become president 
of Nigeria. In an interview with newsmen at his Ikeja 
residence, Chief Abiola appealed to politicians, the media, and 
traditional rulers to prevail on their people to make more 
responsible utterances, in the interest of peace and national 
unity. He recalled that in the annulled presidential elections 
he won more support in Kano than Ogun, his home state, stressing 
that such people deserve better treatment than attacks on pages 
of newspapers. 

</TEXT>

