1900 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0606202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Bengo Province UNITA [National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola] soldiers tried to seize a number 
of government positions, paying dearly for their adventure. In 
three attacks and in one clash with the FAA [Angolan Armed 
Forces] between 13 and 30 May, UNITA abandoned 71 killed on the 
ground, and four of its men were captured. The FAA captured 60 
AKM's, four PKM's, two 60-mm mortars, one RPG-7, one antitank 
missile, 82,000 rounds of ammunition of various caliber, and 
other military equipment. Seven UNITA soldiers turned 
themselves over to government forces during the same period. 
They revealed that right now UNITA intends to recapture the 
locations of Ucua and Gombe and to destroy the bridge over the 
[name indistinct] river. The FAA has already taken measures to 
deal with the situation. 

</TEXT>

