<H3> <TI>   MPLA Said Forcibly Recruiting Youths in Namibia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MPLA Said Forcibly Recruiting Youths in Namibia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0606114694 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0606114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Angola is violating the sovereignty of Namibia with 
the Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party 
[MPLA-PT] secret police involved in the compulsory recruitment 
of Angolan nationals taking refuge in northern Namibia. This 
has been taking place since 4 May with the consent of the 
Namibian authorities, and the Angolan consul in the city of 
Rundu, the capital of Okavango Province. With the current 
compulsory recruitment, hundreds of youths have just been flown 
to Luanda, but the campaign continues and is scheduled to reach 
2,400 men. The Bagani, Omege, Mukwe, Andara, Kangongo, and 
Chobe areas are currently the most affected. In February the 
Namibian president guaranteed that his country would defend the 
international rights of the refugees, but it seems that this is 
no longer so, since he is assisting the Luanda communist 
government. 

</TEXT>

