<H3> <TI>   CNE Chairman Notes Voter Registration Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNE Chairman Notes Voter Registration Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0606194094 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1730 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0606194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Brazao Mazula, chairman of the National 
Electoral Council [CNE], has acknowledged [words indistinct] 
that logistical and transportation problems are hindering the 
smooth registration of voters. Mazula said that as a result of 
the CNE appeal, the government, and the UN Operations in 
Mozambique have already provided vehicles, light aircraft, and 
helicopters which are scheduled to arrive in various provinces 
this week. Mazula was speaking after he registered at Maputo's 
1 May Industrial School for the October elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

