<H3> <TI>   Rights Committee Notes Drop in Violent Deaths </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rights Committee Notes Drop in Violent Deaths </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0706073094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0706073094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Human Rights Committee of South Africa says 
thedeath toll from violence in South Africa has dropped by 60 
percent from 487 in April to 195 last month. The committee says 
in a report that the decrease gives a clear signal that the 
peace, which prevailed during the election days, has been 
maintained. It says that despite ongoing tensions in 
KwaZulu-Natal, violence has continued to drop in this region, 
with the death toll last month being the lowest recorded by the 
committee since January 1993. 

</TEXT>

