<H3> <TI>   North-West Premier Molefe Admitted to Hospital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North-West Premier Molefe Admitted to Hospital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0606185794 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1834 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0606185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mmabatho June 6 SAPA -- North-West Premier Mr Popo 
Molefe was on Monday [6 June] morning "admitted" because of ill 
health, his office said in a brief statement. Asked to 
elaborate, office head Mr Martin Mabiletsa refused "for reasons 
of security" to give further details such as the state of Mr 
Molefe's health or to which institution he had been admitted. 
Provincial Minister of Police Mr Satish Roopa has been 
appointed acting premier. 

</TEXT>

