  [Text] The decree on the constitutional conference has been 
signed into law by the head of state, General Sani Abacha. This 
was announced today in Enugu by the chief of general staff, 
Lieutenant General Oladipo Diya, as a meeting with traditional 
leaders and leaders of thought in the eastern part of the 
country. 
  On the economy, Gen. Diya called on Nigerians to engage more 
seriously in the productive sector for self-reliance. 

